review_text:
I live in a neighborhood of close to 600 homes that has been managed by Kuester for close on to three years now. I’ve been living in this neighborhood for 18 years and have seen four different management companies come and go.

I volunteer on one of the committees in the neighborhood such that I am dependent on getting timely financial information from Kuester and answers to my questions.

What makes a Management company valuable, in my opinion, is the relationship manager. Our relationship manager, Morgan, is outstanding. She responds in a timely manner with clear and concise answers that makes my volunteering job so much easier.

Kuester Management Group is the management company for my community. Back in September, my dog was sick because of lawn chemicals being placed in the lawn without notifying the residents. When I called to notify them that there were multiple sick dogs in the community, they did not seem to care much. The representative on the phone was very nasty and rude to me, the person with a sick dog and elevated liver enzymes. In January, we have a new lawn care company. Yesterday, the lawn care company was putting down Snapshot Pre-emergent weed killer. The granules were on my stairs. I called Kuester and their response was we just received notification about it. It should not matter if the chemicals claim to be non toxic, residents should always be made aware of anything being put down in the lawn. Tamara was very rude at first with me until I explained to her that she was not going to talk to me any kind of way. Tamara went on to say that she has told the lawn care company to give them a week's notice. I feel as though Kuester should be doing a better job of managing the lawn care company especially when we have had sick dogs from chemicals in the past. After speaking with a neighbor, she told me that two weeks ago the lawn care company was spraying something. She called Kuester and received the same information. They have asked the lawn care company to give them notice a week in advance. So what is going to happen the next time? Moving forward, how is the problem going to be resolved or addressed? Will it take more sick dogs to make a point? The job of the management company should be to manage the property! I shouldn't have to do their job by calling the lawn care company and filing a complaint to make them aware of the situation.
owner_answer:
Hello Sade,
What happened in your community is a very unfortunate circumstance and Kuester Management has been looking at what can be done to prevent this in the future. After being notified of the incident, your Board of Directors and Kuester have endeavored to change landscape providers and notification procedures for lawn applications.
With the new landscaper, another unfortunate incident happened where a new hire wanted to be proactive and get a jump start on applying the granules to lawns. The new landscaper has been made aware of the history of this community and why we need the proper notifications. The landscaper will be working to make sure that all concerns of lawn application are properly addressed and that notifications are communicated to the community.
Please do not hesitate to contact us with further concerns and we will be more than happy to help. Thank you for your understanding.

*I am updating my review and improving my rating to 4 stars  to reflect recent communication from Ryan Homes, Kuester (the HOA management company) and the developer to address residents' concerns and clarify the status of our community amenities. They have updated the plan for the amenities center to meet the needs of the community (expanded sports' court to include basketball) and and explanation of the new timeline for the amenities center. I am hopeful that our concerns about the amount of trash left behind by employees/contractors of Ryan Homes will addressed with high expectations communicated with the workers that people live here to ensure their garbage ends up where it belongs.

When we signed a contract at Moore Farm in January of 2020, we expected to have the walking trails abs pool that were used as a selling feature within a reasonable amount of time. However, we have just learned that we will still not have a pool in summer of 2021. The HOA fees are extremely high ($171 per month), but we have zero amenities besides our lawn care. In addition, despite having delayed construction on our amenities center, we have not been consulted on the needs of the community. Apparently there will be a pickle ball court, which no one wants, rather than any kind of sport facility (basketball, tennis, etc.) that might interest the many children in the neighborhood. There is no excuse for the lack of consideration for residents given how much we are paying.

My wife and I don’t usually post negative public reviews. We typically try to contact the person or company privately and resolve it, but they don’t respond to tickets or complaints from their website.

It’s been almost three years since the last house has sold! Our front entrance is not kept up to standard and our street still hasn’t been paved. On the plus side, there are potholes big enough for my kids to jump in and play if it rains. We’ve been asking for positive changes as a community and have continuously gotten the run-around.

If you are a homeowner, steer clear of this company at all costs.

Edit: So I'm a little irked with the service that I received.  While it was fantastic AFTER I visited the office personally on my day off and the problem was addressed the day after, I was also respectfully asked to consider taking down my review.

Again, I wouldn't have left such a review if I was able to get a response or updated on the status of a request.  This request spanned from March 23 - May 16th with multiple e-mails, calls and service requests and was only responded to AFTER I made a personal appearance.

Additionally, I'm not the only resident in my neighborhood to have issues with timely responses.

Respectfully, please make sure there's enough staff or there is a process in place to address requests in a timely manner.  The ability to leave a Google review is one of few ways customers have the ability to keep companies accountable.  I'm paying for a service.  Please respond in a timely manner so I don't have to come in on my days off to have a problem addressed properly.

review_text:
As the landscaping contractor for Carolina Preserve, I work closely with two Kuester staff members.
Freda Halls, Office & Web Administrator, has helped me streamline a weekly service report that goes to all Carolina Preserve residents updating them on the week of yard service. Freda has formatted the report to simplify the uploading and distribution of the report into Carolina Preserve’s web portal. This task was a lot more time consuming and Freda has helped improve this process. I also lean very heavily on her to assist getting me resident contact information to address work-orders. Freda is an excellent asset to Kuester staff.

Michelle Greene, Director of Operations, is extremely instrumental in allowing me to be as effective as possible. We work with each other daily on resident work-orders and any major issues Carolina Preserve’s residents may have with our daily services of yard-work. Michelle understands our contract and speaks to residents that may not fully understand what services are performed under the contract. This is huge, this property has over 1,300+ homes to service plus common area covering services for yard-work and as well as irrigation services. We meet daily and perform frequent drive –arounds to ensure services are up to standard. Michelle also updates the General Manager of major issues and I meet with the GM regularly as well. Having these professional relationships are huge for me & our crew to handle this property.
Thank you,
Allen Jones Account Mgr.

community in which residents love to live.

Jeff Campbell has been a terrific asset on getting our HOA committee off the ground!  Always available for any issues and questions. o glad he is aprt of the team!

review_text: I give Kuester Management Group ZERO stars because that is the type of management they have given to me as a Homeowner at Riviera II.  Homeowners are left in the dark in how our Riviera II Board and Kuester are running our HOA as minutes are not distributed or posted. Since April 2015 to date, only seven months of minutes have been posted to our community website out of 23 months!  And, our Kuester community website still doesn't show correct board members that were elected almost four months ago!  I would expect better service from a management group which homeowners' dues pay for.  After our Board and Kuester terminated our landscaper with no notice to homeowners, Kuester signed a contract with a so-called landscaper who left all homeowners angry throughout 2016 as our grounds were repeatedly either ignored, ill-kept or damaged -- and Kuester and our Board ignored complaints until homeowners started to band together and our former landscaper was rehired. Now we have to deal with the aftermath expense in repair of grounds.   I would expect a management company to immediately recommend the dismissal of ANY contractor who so clearly violated his contract -- esp. since the horrible landscaping was so visible to all.  But instead, Kuester praised contractor, made excuses for him and allowed him to be paid while not providing the services he was being paid for. It was Kuester's representative's signature on this contract.  Kuester's website advertises "Contractor negotiations and selection." Beware of that! For any HOA considering a management company, please visit the Riviera II community first -- in comparison to HOAs with other management companies. Good luck also to other homeowners in getting Kuester to respond to your emails and issues -- you will be waiting a very long time.
owner_answer: Both Kuester and the Board of Directors have made numerous attempts and gone above and beyond for Ms. Werth.

review_text: If I could leave 0 stars.. I would. I have had the WORST experience with kuester management in so many ways I don't know where to begin . From the poor customer service of the people that answer the phones , to the lack of service provided. I had a irrigation leak in my front yard for 5 weeks, and made multiple phone calls before some one found it urgent enough to get it fixed . Once it was fixed, they left trash bags in my yard, flags, landscaping rocks moved, and my yard a disheveled mess. I was told I would also get sod in that area 4 weeks ago , and have yet to see anything , and my yard is still disaster, isn't landscaping included in the 125$ payment I make per month?? . And let's not forget the act of congress that I had to go through to get a fence in my back yard.. they said they would approve within 28 days and after much harassment and phone calls , I finally got an approval letter in 34 days. I could go on for days , but my blessings go out to you if you have this company as your hoa.

excellent work!
I would recommend kuester management group..
